# App Creation Rules
When creating a new Django app under `backend/hirethon_template/`, follow this structure:

my_app/
├── __init__.py
├── admin.py
├── apps.py
├── api/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── serializers.py
│   └── views.py
├── context_processors.py      # Optional, only if needed
├── forms.py                   # All app forms must go here
├── managers.py                # Custom model managers
├── migrations/
│   ├── __init__.py
├── models.py
├── tasks.py                   # Celery or async tasks
├── tests/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── test_models.py
│   ├── test_api.py
│   ├── test_views.py
│   ├── test_forms.py
│   ├── test_urls.py
│   └── factories.py
├── urls.py
└── views.py                   # Regular Django views only
